     <h5>Review of Westmont’s Internship Program</h5> 
     <p>Students planning to earn credit for an internship are required to take a concurrent course. The seminar style courses offer practical application of academic theories and develop civic, social, and vocational skills. When a student earns <em>major</em> credit for an internship, the experience is called a <em>practicum</em>. When a student takes the elective internship course (APP-190 or APP-190SS) the experience is called an <em>internship</em>. The following departments schedule practicum courses on a regular or semi-regular basis: </p> 
     <table width="" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" bordercolor="#000000"> 
      <tbody>
       <tr> 
